      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TINKERBELLA (1) was comfortably accounted for when ninth last time out over 1100m at this track. That followed a win at Gatton at the previous outing. Suitably placed so anticipating a better run this time. RUSSIAN RIPPER (7) was quickly into stride from the rails draw last start but emptied late to finish seventh over 1100m here. Will go forward and is expected to be in the finish. EXOSTOVA (5) finished out of the money when fresh from a spell two starts back then he was never in contention and was beaten 11 lengths when eighth over 1100m at this circuit three weeks ago. Best figures measure up nicely and is sure to run well. DO WHAT I SAY (8) wound up strongly last time out to finish 0.6 lengths adrift in second over 1200m at Warwick. Solid top-three prospects.",
